Western ODM delegates will meet on Friday in Kakamega for regional delegates&rsquo; conference to discuss party primaries.The meeting will be chaired by party leader Raila Odinga. The members are drawn from Kakamega, Bungoma, Vihiga, Busia and Trans Nzoia counties. More than 2,500 delegates will meet for the first time at the Masinde Muliro University of Science and Technology multipurpose hall to make declarations ahead of next year&rsquo;s general election.The Western Region ODM Delegates Convention has been convened by deputy party leader and Kakamega Governor Wycliffe Oparanya.On Sunday, Busia ODM delegates met at Texas Hotel in Busia town. They said delegates want an assurance the party primaries will be free and fair.MCA aspirant Grace Omasete said the 2007 and 2013 primaries were unfair. She said, however, she has remained loyal to the party.Marachi West MCA Gomba Sewe said they reject flawed nominations.Amukura West MCA hopeful Pekol Mrade said he will wants an assurance from Raila that first-timers will get a fair chance. He said they might be locked out, despite their popularity.Busia ODM deputy secretary Peter Odima said the party lost the Nambale parliamentary seat to UDF, after their candidate was locked out at the primaries. &ldquo;We need to play a fair game in the nominations,&rdquo; he said.Elected woman MCA Florence Opemi urged peaceful campaigns.Busia ODM secretary Innocent Oluku said only accredited aspirants will be allowed at the conference. He said employed aspirants can write letters of intent to the national secretariat, who can defer membership to February 2017, when they will register.